  <title>Gio.Drive.prototype.stop</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function stop(flags: <link xref="Gio.MountUnmountFlags">Gio.MountUnmountFlags</link>, mount_operation: <link xref="Gio.MountOperation">Gio.MountOperation</link>, cancellable: <link xref="Gio.Cancellable">Gio.Cancellable</link>, callback: <link xref="Gio.AsyncReadyCallback">Gio.AsyncReadyCallback</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_drive_stop()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Asynchronously stops a drive.</p>  <p>When the operation is finished, <code>callback</code> will be called.
You can then call <link xref="Gio.stop_finish"/> to obtain the
result of the operation.</p>
  <p>Since 2.22</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>flags</code></title>
  <p>flags affecting the unmount if required for stopping.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>mount_operation</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.MountOperation"/> or <code>null</code> to avoid
    user interaction.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>cancellable</code></title>
  <p>optional <link xref="Gio.Cancellable"/> object, <code>null</code> to ignore.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>callback</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.AsyncReadyCallback"/>, or <code>null</code>.</p>
</item>
